inn1.comm: angled in fullish outside off, moving away, left alone
shuffles across to a length ball and defends
127 kph, straightening on off stump, bouncing too, down to third man as he shuflfes and stabs at it
excellent line first ball to Gayle, 125 kph only, but straightens after being angles across, Gayle pushes at it, beaten
he was gone by miles had the throw hit, Gayle pushing a length ball on off towards cover and charging down, he wanted the single, Charles gets away, barely
full delivery outside off squeezed past point
swinging in to leg stump, from back of a length, rolls fine
tight line, straightening after being anged in from over the stumps, left alone about a foot or two outside off
slightly wider outside off stump, holding its line again, he takes a step out and lets it go
another one in the same area outside off, straightening again, left alone
Gayle is already tired of leaving, he charges out to a pitched up delivery just outside off stump again, and looks to go over extra cover, a thick edge flies over second slip's leap

lovely delivery to end, Gayle coming out again,  the ball holding its line again, and just beating the outside edge, that is a tough angle to survive against, let alone loft over extra cover, angling in and then swerving away
defends a length ball to off
now Charles has some charging out to do, and does not get into trouble like Gayle did, to the pitch of the delivery around off and mows it high and straight down the ground
and again, things are already looking ominous for this thin attack, Charles steps out again, he is not quite to the pitch this time, but still drills it past the non-striker, made the umpire duck
width outside off, punched wide of point
steps forward and eases it down to mid off, who is quite deep, with Gayle and Charles doing what they are
beaten, the angle across him taking it away, past a weak push
shuffles across initially to counter the angle, but this one straightens down the leg side, a better line would have tested him
goes full, around the blockhole, 128 kph, but the line is again down the pads, away to fine leg
he bowled a few testing deliveries to Gayle in the fourth ODI, firing them in on the pads and then getting them to straighten, this one is angled in, but slips down leg
better line around off stump, pushed away towards cover
that took off, from back of a length, there were lots of these from Oram in the previous game, Gayle stabs it away past second slip
into the batsman with the angle and worked square
short of a length, angled across, 125 kph, punched to extra cover
back of a length again, ending around off stump, patted away softly
this is a bonus for New Zealand, Gayle could have done potentially decisive damage, a short and wide delivery he gets, he goes after the cut, but point times his leap too well
pitched up, pushed back to the bowler
he takes on mid on, the second time West Indies have gone for a very tight single today, and makes it just in time as the throw hits
he is going to go his way, throws his bat at a full and wide one, gets it safely over point, surely not the direction he was looking for
a shout for lbw, but that pitched outside leg stump, Smith in a mess as he plays all around a length ball
this went in the intended direction alright, not quite off the middle, though, without any foot movement, he goes after a pitched up ball and lofts it over extra cover
same approach, wants to lean out and drive one angled across now, beaten
again he is troubled by one straightening as he misses a push, to one on middle and leg, but again it looked to have landed outside leg
goes full, around off at 130 kph, is worked in front of square leg, he wanted the second, the throw was quick to prevent that
defended to the off side
angled in to middle and leg, worked behind square
right on middle and off, 132 kph, pitched up, he gets across, behind the line and blocks
length ball defended to short extra cover

one of those that takes off has done Charles in, Oram in the first game, Southee today, kicks and bites from just back of a length outside off, Charles is getting across and is surprised by the lift, and tamely lobs it to point
back of a length, pushed to mid off
this is totally unconvincing and absolutely needless at this stage from Smith, wide and full one, he goes after it, and edges it past the man at slip
good carry with the angle outside off, left alone
gets across, cover the stumps and lets it go past with the angle outside off
straightens, he has done that consistently today, but the line has been too much down the pads, and Samuels leans back and slightly across and flicks it away behind square
pitched up, holding its line on off, he shuffles and defends from the crease
not far from off stump, straightish length ball, Smith moves far across, and shoulders arms

that looked plumb, he has been getting that front leg across and awkwardly getting away, this time he does not, length ball skids and bounces past the bat swing, and strikes him in front of off and middle, he's given, and even the review cannot save him, no evidence of an inside edge, that was hitting top of middle, according to the ball tracker, on-field call stays
left alone outside off
defended down the pitch
that moved in slightly from a length, but was far enough to be left alone
bounce and straightening outside off stump, lets it go again
another dangerous single, moves across and pushes behind point, throw misses, looked very tight, but West Indies get some overthrows
128 kph, neat carry from a good length, left alone with the angle
right forward to defend a length ball down the pitch
very well played, this one lifted a lot outside off stump, but DJ leans back a tad and controls the punch past point
eases a pitched up ball down to mid off
there is some of that awkward bounce from just back of a length, Samuels handled it the best in the previous ODI among the Windies batsmen, he does so again, drops it down softly to third man
gets behind the line and defends down the track
short for the pull, around shoulder high, and he swivels to hit it to deep square
shuffles across and defends a length ball around off
full toss on the pads, worked behind square leg, pulled back inside the rope
holding its line a tad from back of a length, pushed away to off
defended to short extra cover's left
121 kph, nipping in from short of a length, defended
another one nips in, back of a length again, he takes a hand off the bat as he stabs it away
pitched up, around off 123 kph, defended, he is pretty nippy off the pitch at the moment, Ellis,
reaches out to a fuller one outside off and smothers it awkwardly
opens the face to a 121.8 kph length ball outside off, runs it to point, he is definitely appearing sharper than 121 kph
slower one, 114 kph, nudged to square leg
worked to the right of midwicket
away to deep square leg
flat length ball played out to backward point
83.5 kph, played out to square leg
spins in but down the leg side from a length
midwicket dives to his left to stop a punch
defended to backward point, decent over in the end
short of a length, worked along to deep square leg
moves across to defend a 114 kph length ball on off
gets behind the line with a big shuffle and pushes with the angle to midwicket
puts in more effort into this bouncer, 129 kph, rises outside off stump, too much
back of a length ball pushed down to long on
gets bat in front of pad to defend
too short, 87.8 kph, and Bravo opens up to pound it over midwicket
big shuffle across again and a nudge towards fine leg
eases a flat and shortish one to point from the crease
that's gone, he uses his feet well to spinners, Samuels, comes down and launches it over long on with the spin
length ball spinning in, worked straight to square leg
full toss into the pads, punched to long on
pushed to short extra cover
87.5 kph, full around off, defended
comes out, takes it low on the full and drills it through the bowler's hands, Flynn ended up changing the path of the ball, made it straighter
flat, pushed out to point
moves out of the crease again, and pushes to long on
119 kph back of a length ball played out to point
awkward bounce from back of a length, but Samuels tackles it very well, once again, runs it down to third man softly
and Bravo almost gets into trouble to a similar ball, he opens the face too much, plays early, and almost plays on
more bounce, from a good length now, Bravo tentatively defends
111 kph slower one, Bravo swivels across for the pull, but inside edges it onto thigh pad
shuffles across, and keeps down a back of a length ball
122 kph, he has been nipping them in, kept out with some trouble to the off side
113 kph on middle, nudged towards square leg
pitched up, and driven nicely, past point, who stops it as it slows down close to the rope
back and across a tad and works it behind square leg off the pad
behind the line of a 113 kph length ball around off and defends
much fuller, he leans forward low and pushes to off
holding its line outside off, left alone
takes a step out, and leaves a 126 kph length ball well outside off
he still gets the single to third man, width provided and he runs it past point's dive
that bounced a lot, Bravo has to hop and keep it down towards point
nice carry to the keeper as it straightens outside off, he lets it go
back of a length ball, punched through extra cover
reaches forward to a pitched up ball, pushes to extra cover
sharp short ball, 128 kph, he drops the wrists, and bends out of the way quickly
moves across, and works it to square leg
into the pads, worked in the air, but well past short fine leg, KW puts in the dive and somehow prevents the ball from touching the rope, as it rolls under his legs
plays a length ball from the crease, looking to work it to leg but pushes it back to the bowler
crack! that has raced through the off-side infield, on the front foot, opens the face late to drive it past point
straight outside off, left alone without fuss
leans out and gracefully eases a full delivery to point
can't get it through, tries to punch a length ball through covers, but cannot beat the field
rising as it carries to the keeper after being left alone outside off
angled in, worked straight to midwicket
coming in, stabbed away to the off side with an inside edge
tough chance, but dropped, Bravo gets far across and pushes a length ball in the air towards the bowler, Ellis dives to his right in his followthrough, gets a hand to it, but it pops out
moving far across again, too much, the ball rolls off pad to fine leg
not getting the single, leans across and works it to midwicket
beats him first ball with a full ball angled across from round the stumps, Bravo going for a big drive
similar ball, he connects this time, but drives it straight to point
inside edge to vacant short leg as he pushes forward
flat and into the pads, swept down to fine leg
skips out, and goes over the non-striker, just beats long off's dive
and again, this time he moves down and goes through midwicket, but there is a man in the deep to cut it off
that nipped back in quite sharply from outside off, Samuels was across and outside off to defend, it went to a diving keeper on the bounce, looked to be bit of both pad and inside edge
short of a length, defended
opens the face and runs a length ball to point
had mid off picked up the ball cleanly, the single would have been much tighter, Samuels pushing a very full one and setting off
mistimes a pull to deep square leg
that was worth an appeal at least, shuffling across too much, and taking it on the pad in front of middle and leg, looked high, and lot of angle though, Southee has something to say to Samuels
pushed away to mid off
Bravo tried to get out of the way, but Samuels eventually hit him on the right glove as he took evasive action
whipped to midwicket
comes out again, the ball spins in down the pads, and is worked down to fine leg as he takes a hand off the bat

Guptill with an outstanding take at extra cover, Samuels was looking in control, but this time he tried to punch a back of a length ball that bounced extra, and he weakly pushed it to extra cover's left, where Guptill dived full-stretch to snap it up low with both hands
gets a yorker first up, calmly jams it out
cutting in from back of a length, and Pollard inside edges it onto thigh pad, it rolls away close to off stump
a huge stride forward to defend a pitched up ball
bouncer, outside off, he gets head out of the way
stabs a back of a length ball to the leg side off a thick inside edge, takes the single as Southee goes for the ball
bat in front of pad to work it to midwicket
bashes a full delivery angled across, wide of sweeper cover
86.6 kph, pushes right forward and keeps it out
no stopping this one, splits the gap between long off and sweeper cover, KW going too full with the angle across
no rescue job from Pollard today, this one is not as full as the previous one, angled across just outside off, Pollard drags it straight to midwicket
tossed up, defended to the leg side
starts with a length ball angling across, not too much width there, Bravo defends it towards the off side
pitches it up, Bravo gets behind the line of that and defends solidly down the track
shorter this time and just outside off, stands tall and punches it towards point
back of a length ball outside off, Bravo shuffles across and thumps it towards cover
sends that away towards midwicket, the fielder stops it just beyond the circle, Thomas wants two, but Bravo sends him back, perhaps remembering his run-out from the third ODI
shortish and just outside off, pushed towards cover by Thomas, Boult keeping it tight around off
on off stump, on a length, defended
slightly wider outside off, blocked off the front foot
on the pads, clipped towards square leg
once more, this time wider of the fielder to get a single
on the pads, whipped towards midwicket, where a diving stop prevents the single
down the leg side from Boult, off the thigh pad and wide of the keeper for four leg-byes
length ball is driven on the up towards cover
short of length and just outside off, stays in the crease and opens the face to guide the ball towards backward point
punched off the back foot towards cover where a diving Guptill fields
bit of width there, slashed past backward point for a single, Bravo moves to 20 off 60, not his usual strike-rate shall we say
full and on the pads, squeezed towards square leg for a single, Thomas is off the mark
full and outside off, driven towards sweeper cover
length ball on middle stump, defended off the front foot to the off side
pitched up, driven crisply towards cover, fielded well there
down the leg side and that is a wide, Williamson has been bowling from round the wicket
on the pads, clipped towards square leg
driven down the ground towards long-off for a single
down the leg side for another wide
keeps it on the pads, defended towards square leg
pushing that out towards short extra cover from the crease
a bit wide outside off, punched off the back foot towards point, not with much power, a diving stop prevents the run
angling in towards off stump, length ball is solidly defended
touch shorter and just outside off, dabbed wide of backward point for a quick run
short of length, heading for off stump, blocked back towards the bowler
nudges this one behind backward square leg for a single, that was heading down leg from Boult
length ball spins in, defended towards midwicket
there's the Twenty20 Bravo who has been missing much of today, short from Nicol, sits up for Bravo, who gets the front leg out of the way and hammers that over deep midwicket for six
gently tapped towards midwicket
length ball is pushed back towards the bowler
full and outside off, takes the outside edge past the keeper, the chase is on, the fielder puts in a dive at the third man boundary but can't stop that streaky four
length ball on middle and leg, defended
low full toss driven to wide long off
flashes at a fuller one outside off, gets it to sweeper cover
fired in flat at 93 kph, stabbed away to midwicket
90 kph, leans forward, finds midwicket again
pushed off the front foot to extra cover
squeezes the drive past extra cover, sweeper cover cuts it off
full and across from round the stumps, cracked to sweeper cover
flat and on a length, pushed towards point
runs it fine and wide of fine leg off the pad
he is persisting with the full length to Bravo just outside off, and Bravo crashes it to the left of long off
tossed up on off, pushed to short extra cover
walks out and pushes on the full to long off
118 kph, pitched up, he pushes it softly to short extra cover
turned with a flourish through square leg, from around off
short, sitting up, he slams down the pull along the ground, wide of deep square leg
he's gone for that shot every time the opportunity has been there, full outside off, he smashes it past extra cover with that eager full followthrough
pushed to mid on for one
pitched up, but slow at 108 kph, he checks his stroke and plays it out
down the pads, and he works for a single to square leg
dabs it to third man
very slow, 108 kph, length ball cutting in around off, can only punch it to the bowler
another slower one, and he ends up flat-batting it down to long off, was in the air for some time
now Thomas goes after a pitched up delivery outside off, in DJ Bravo fashion, lofts it vigorously high over extra cover
punches one coming in from a length down to long on
batting more freely now, works it from outside off, big followthrough, one leg in the air, through square leg
pushes a low full toss straight past the non-striker, would have wanted to get more power on that, long on will field this one
this time he has got a lot of power on another full toss, but not much timing, and it goes into the hands of deep square leg, who fumbles but holds on as he tumbles forward
off the mark first ball, moves across and works it from off in front of square leg
whipped through to deep midwicket, again from outside off
single with a nudge behind square leg
gets across outside off stump, gets too close to the line and stabs away a length ball
Sammy goes without doing any damage, the line was wide enough for the cut, he went for it in Caribbean fashion too, very hard, but there was too much bounce, and keeper snaps up the edge
126 kph length ball run to point with an open face
length ball on off, defended
bounce from back of a length, he opens the face and runs it to point
length ball pushed away to point
beats him outside off now, as he reaches out a widish length ball
tries to angle in the yorker, not quite full, worked in front of square leg
thick inside edge down to fine leg as he looks to drive
very full, on the stumps, pushed to long on
another attempted yorker, almost gets it right, dug out to mid off
runs it down to short third man
flashes at it outside off, to short third again
sends it very low and full into the pads, he gets across enough to flick it fine down leg
well forward to defend a pitched up ball to the bowler
punched to the bowler from the crease
worked in front of square leg
punches a length ball on the up, to sweeper cover
pitched up, he mistimes a slog to deep midwicket
gets to his fifty with a push down to long on, been a struggle mostly, but he has hung in, unlike the previous game, and that is refreshing
pushed to extra cover
gets the yorker in, on the stumps, he jams down the bat on it
pulled to deep midwicket
122 kph and full outside off, he cannot run it down to third man, misses
wide and low full toss, he runs it down to third man this time, but would have wanted to go squarer
wide, he gets down and drives hard to sweeper cover
gets bat right forward to push to long on
another full toss, another wicket, low this time, into the pads, and flicked, with back leg in the air, of course, to midwicket on the edge of the circle
and right away he dabs a wide ball to back ward point
smacks a short of a length ball past short cover's dive
finds cow corner with precision, mows a full ball angled in through midwicket, deep midwicket runs across, long on dives, both in vain
another full toss, finds long on this time
width outside off, cut away to sweeper cover, with some style
low full toss from round the stumps, eased to long on
that should have gone, short and flat outside off, bashed to extra cover
goes leg side now, and gets the runs, front leg out of the way, and power it in front of square leg, just over the cameraman beyond the rope
moves about in the crease, gets a wide full toss and slogs it straight over the bowler
very full delivery, wants to repeat the stroke, gets it towards long off this time
they go for a sharp single, and make it safely, with a push towards cover

confusion, and Russell would have been gone by several metres, he wanted to get to the other end, Narine pushed it towards point, Russell  was more than halfway up the pitch as Narine hesitated, the throw missed at the non-striker's
not a bad stroke at all, punched gracefully wide of long off
yet another full toss, angled in, and disappears over deep midwicket
dear me, New Zealand show no signs of letting up on the full tosses, here's one more, Russell murders it over square leg
and he compensates, too much, with a full and wide delivery outside off
no stopping the full tosses, wide outside off now, swung to cow corner, deep midwicket manages to slap it back in from very close to the rope, long on is around to throw it in
gets width, and dabs it towards point
Narine gives it away, when he should have been giving the strike to Russell with four overs left, swings a full one from outside off straight to long on
keeps out the yorker on off, 124 kph, jams it to leg
near-yorker outside off, he does well to drive it to sweeper cover
high full toss, outside off, Best calmly pats it away
moving away from wide outside off, and called a wide
they take the single with an open-faced push towards point
Russell keeps strike, squeezes out a full ball to point
that almost took out another NZ bowler, Southee was fortunate he was not that close to the line of this full-blown swing from Russell, which sent a full delivery screaming past the bowler
full ball, powerful swing again, a single to long on now
keeps out a pitched up ball off the front foot
Best gets a full toss now, and sensibly gives strike to Russell with a tuck to deep midwicket
saw him stepping far across, and floated it very wide outside off
another one wide outside off, just inside the marker, Russell reaches out but misses
once more, low full toss, not as wide as the previous ones, Russell swings and misses
very well done, leans forward and works it from outside off to long on, strike given to Russell
he has started missing these full ones outside off regularly now
full again, wide outside off, he is ready this time, gets down on a knee and smashes it, but straight to sweeper cover
right on off, length ball, pushed to short extra cover, cannot get the run
gets the single now with a steer to third man off a length ball
slams a very full one down to long off, and brings up a hard-hitting fifty, which has propped up West Indies from 160 for 7
now they are getting predictable with this full and wide stuff outside off, Russell has good reach, he bends the knee and wallops it over extra cover

another one, this is as powerful and as clean as a No 9 will ever get, Russell going after another wide one, it was not far from sweeper cover, he even got to it, but ended up parrying it into the boundary
down to long on for one
squeezes a very full delivery past the non-striker to long on
misses out this time, full and wide outside off, almost a wide, Russell cannot connect
and again, full, wide and coming in a tad, Russell misses for the last time this innings

inn2.comm: 138 kph, back of a length, but wide and pushed past cover for a couple
Best strikes first over again, superb reflex catch from Bravo at a short position in front of square leg, full, into the pads, could have been flicked away anywhere, but Nicol finds Bravo, who
back of a length again, 142 kph, enough width to punch past cover
that has been put away, full delivery, outside off, driven off the front foot past point
coming in, 140 kph, but too far outside off
lovely, 141 kph, taking off from back of a length, holding its line too, Baz did well to get beaten actually, that could have been easily edged behind
sharp, straight, good length outside off, left alone, 127 kph
right forward to a pitched up ball outside off, defends
wants to punch a length ball off the back foot, straight to short extra cover
moves away, but pitched far outside off, left alone
130 kph length ball pushed to the bowler
length ball pushed to midwicket
bounce from a good length, hits the bat hard at 141 kph, defended to the off side
short wide outside off, he goes for a cut, beaten
wide again, short again, this time the cut flies over backward point
gets half-forward and defends a length ball
that hurried off a length, thick inside edge runs to point as he defends
angled in, good length, 141 kph, worked to square leg, throw comes in at the non-striker's and runs to the long off boundary, off Guptill's bat
outside edge, past second slip, to third man as he pushes hard from the crease to a back of a length ball
punched from the crease again, to mid off
full into the stumps at 132 kph, pushed back to the bowler
moves right forward and defends a good length delivery to short extra
more width to McCullum, and he goes after it, hit it just over Sammy at short cover-point, he did get his hands up, but the ball had already zoomed over by then
takes a step out and allows a straight delivery to go outside off
140 kph, zips back of a length far outside off, left alone
bouncer, dug in, Guptill ducks, too much bounce, says the square leg umpire, he's right
whoa, that is massive, Guptill has put front foot out and creamed a pitched up delivery into the grass banks beyond deep extra cover
solidly forward, defended to cover
no movement, into the pads from back of a length and he uses the pace to whip it behind square, fine leg runs and dives across to keep it out, super effort
that bounced, but he had it under control, drops it close to the pitch on off and takes one
pitched up, quick, but no movement in the air or off the pitch for Best, defended to extra cover
no trouble at all, moving across to a length ball and punching it down the pitch, fell just in front of the bowler
short ball dug in, he is hit on the body as he misses the pull
mistimes it to the leg side as he moves across and opens up to try and force it away
biff! Russell goes down in his followthrough, taking evasive action, as Guptill powers a pitched up ball straight over him
goes for a yorker, 136 kph, down the pads and rolls away to short fine
they continue to give width to McCullum, and he continues peppering the off side rope with cut strokes
works a length ball to midwicket
pitched up now, on the stumps, he gets bat around pad just in time to defend
on off stump, good length, defended to short extra
gets the outside edge, but it scurries past slip, and beats third man, Sammy has hands on his knees, Guptill walking right across to off stump and defending
defended to extra cover
tight line around off, punched, to extra cover again
offspinner tossed up full, 85 kph, defended
into middle and leg, fullish again, defended off a thick inside edge to short fine leg
shortish, offspinner turns in, and Baz opens up to pull it through midwicket
works an ofspinner behind square leg
nudged behind square leg
length offspinner, he moves across and turns it square on leg
length ball angled in, punched from the crease to wide mid on
behind the line to defend a pitched up ball on off
mistimes an attempted push to off, back to the bowler
back and across to punch to mid off, Sammy slowing down the flow of runs
angled in, gets bat around front leg to work it to deep square
width, but there is not much pace to work with at 126 kph, he mistimes the cut to point
pushes forward to a full offspinner and gets a single to long on
offspinner turning in full, pushed off the front foot to short extra cover
nudged to midwicket
tossed up full, defended down the pitch
moves about in the crease and works an offspinner square on leg
an appeal for caught behind turned down as this one carries down the leg side, not wided as well, has to be pad then
around off stump again is Sammy, McCullum moves across and punches a length ball to the bowler
another one on off stump, this time he punches it past the non-striker to long on
lofted over midwicket, used the angle into him, and dispatched it with a straight followthrough
goes for the single with a push to cover, rightly sent back
played out to midwicket
length ball, pushed to midwicket again
tries a reverse sweep, to a straightening delivery on middle, misses
full delivery pushed away, Gayle tumbles to stop it at midwicket
angled away, but pitching outside leg, and ending on leg too, it is shortish as well, Baz needs no more invitation to pull it through square leg
gets behind the line and defends

the angle works, flicked from round the stumps, drifts away, good length, Baz looks to defend, it did not turn away much, just enough to take the edge and settle into slip's hands, this is not an angle he's used much
angled across into middle and leg, defended down the pitch
pushed off the front foot, short extra cover dives to his left and fields
Sammy stops a straight push in his followthrough
wide of point with a push for one
Sammy produces an outside edge second time with some bounce from a good length, this one bounces to slip
pitched up, eases it to wide mid off
Narine continues round the wicket, around the pads, defended off the front foot

an lbw appeal, turned down, West Indies think of a review, decide against it, that looked to be pitching outside leg, replays show that was pitching on leg, a review and that decision would have been overturned, pitching on leg, and going on to hit the top of leg
blocked off the back foot towards mid-on
flighted this time, full and on leg stump, paddled down to fine leg
full ball on the pads, defended to square leg
short of length and on the pads, defended towards mid-off
back of length ball outside off, pushed towards point
length ball angling in, punched towards long-on
short of length and pushed towards extra cover, tight single to Narine, whose throw misses at the non-striker's end, Taylor would have just made it
length ball on off stump, once again no room to work with, blocked
just a bit of width outside off, dabbed down to third man for a single
pitched up and outside off, worked towards long-on
from over the wicket, length offspinner, played off the back foot towards cover
clipped off the front foot towards midwicket
short from Narine, not punished, it went straight, on off and middle, pushed back to the bowler
the big offbreak chases Taylor as he looks to make room, Taylor manages to push that towards point for a quick single
a quicker ball spinning away, starts outside off and Guptill reads it early, left alone
length ball on the pads, worked behind square leg for a quick run
length, drives off the back foot towards the bowler, who moves to his right to collect
short of length and outside off, defended towards the off side off the front foot
angling in towards off stump, looks to work it down to third man, can't beat the man in the ring
Sammy again nags away at off stump, blocked off the front foot
short of length and once more Guptill guides it towards third man for a single
offspinner tossed up and straightening on middle, defended
shuffles across and punches a length ball to midwicket
